<h1>
 DotGNU - Making the Web Work for You!
</h1>
<p>
 We're building something that could be called an "operating system
 for the internet" - a collection of tools that allow software
 components to interact with each other over the internet.  The
 most impressive parts are currently <a href="&nav.pnet;">DotGNU
 Portable.NET</a> which builds a C# compiler, class library, and
 related development tools, and <a href="&nav.phpgw;">phpGroupWare</a>,
 a multi-user web-based GroupWare suite, which also serves to provide
 a good collection of webservice components, all of which can be accessed
 through XML-RPC so that you can easily integrate them into webservice
 applications of your own.  The <a href="&nav.phpgw;">DGEE</a> webservice
 server is also moving forward nicely.
</p>
<p>
 DotGNU, a project of GNU, is really a meta-project that will consist 
 of a good number of such <a href="&nav.projects;">software development
 projects</a>. The main objectives of DotGNU are to build a 
 <a href="&nav.arch;">webservices platform</a> and a <a href="&nav.auth;">
 Virtual Identities</a> system.
</p>
<p>
 Now Dotgnu news is also available as an RSS feed. <a href="index.rdf" class="linksbody"><img valign="bottom" border="0" src="g/xml.jpg"/></a>
</p>
